Epic: Enhance Workspace Management for Metadata Comparison and Commit/Reject Workflow
Epic Description:
This epic focuses on improving the workspace management workflow for metadata comparison and commit/reject operations. The enhancements include creating read-only workspaces, comparing workspace files for metadata changes, and implementing robust APIs for commit/reject processes. Additional features such as error handling, notifying users of unsupported changes, and reporting unrecognized nodes will ensure a seamless and accurate workflow. The deliverables also include email notifications for critical failures and the ability to list and manage workspaces by series group and ID.

Stories
Story 1: Make S3 Filesystem Read-Only
Description: Ensure that workspace folders in the S3 filesystem are read-only and cannot be overwritten using tools like JD GUI.
Acceptance Criteria:
Workspace folders are read-only by default.
Any attempt to overwrite these folders triggers an appropriate error message.
Story 2: Compare Workspace Files for Metadata Changes
Description: Automate the process of comparing workspace files to detect metadata changes, including those not explicitly listed in the spec spreadsheet.
Acceptance Criteria:
Comparison covers all nodes mentioned in the spec spreadsheet.
Unrecognized nodes are flagged and logged.
Users are notified of unsupported changes (e.g., changes to the analysis span).
Detailed results of valid and invalid changes are presented to the user.
Story 3: Create DynamoDB Table for WIP Workspaces
Description: Implement a DynamoDB table to store WIP workspace metadata for comparisons and build associated APIs.
Acceptance Criteria:
DynamoDB table is created and populated with WIP workspace metadata.
APIs support:
Adding WIP workspaces.
Updating WIP workspaces.
Retrieving WIP workspaces by series group ID and series ID.
APIs are tested for performance and accuracy.
Story 4: Implement Service to List WIP Workspaces
Description: Build a service to list all WIP workspaces by series group ID and series ID.
Acceptance Criteria:
Endpoint to list all series group IDs with WIP workspaces.
Endpoint to list all series IDs within a series group with WIP workspaces.
Endpoint to list all WIP workspaces for a series ID.
Provide detailed information on valid/invalid changes and log comparison failures.
Story 5: Build Commit/Reject API
Description: Develop an API to handle commit and reject operations for WIP workspaces, including metadata updates and cleanup tasks.
Acceptance Criteria:
Commit operation updates the metadata store and marks the workspace as completed.
Reject operation discards changes, deletes the workspace, and updates the DynamoDB table.
If write operations fail, users are notified with clear instructions to retry.
UI reflects successful or failed commit/reject operations.
Story 6: Enhance Error Handling for Commit Operations
Description: Ensure robust error handling for unsupported changes and unrecognized nodes during the commit process.
Acceptance Criteria:
Service checks all JD nodes mentioned in the spreadsheet for validity.
Unrecognized or unsupported changes are flagged before commit.
Users cannot commit until all errors are resolved.
Story 7: Email Notifications for Critical Failures
Description: Implement an email notification system to alert SATS support of critical failures during workspace operations.
Acceptance Criteria:
Emails are triggered for critical failures, including workspace save errors and metadata inconsistencies.
Email includes detailed failure information for troubleshooting.
Story 8: Finalize Service for Creating Read-Only Workspaces
Description: Enhance the service to create read-only workspaces by incorporating pipeline logs.
Acceptance Criteria:
Service creates read-only workspaces with metadata from the pipeline logs.
Bulk update functionality does not retrigger workspace creation automatically.
If bulk update triggers deletion of existing WIP workspaces, ensure proper logging and notification.
Story 9: Investigate Bulk Update Impact on WIP Workspaces
Description: Decide and implement the behavior for bulk updates in relation to existing WIP workspaces.
Acceptance Criteria:
Bulk updates can optionally delete existing WIP workspaces.
Commit operations for a series automatically delete all WIP workspaces for that series.
Requirement alignment with business stakeholders is documented.
Story 10: Approval Workflow for Commit/Reject
Description: Investigate and define if a dual-approval workflow is required for commit/reject operations.
Acceptance Criteria:
Approval workflow is either implemented or documented as not required at this stage.
If needed, additional approval steps are logged and auditable.
Acceptance Criteria for the Epic:
All stories are implemented, tested, and integrated.
Users can seamlessly compare, commit, or discard changes for WIP workspaces.
Metadata consistency is maintained with robust error handling.
All JD nodes, including unrecognized ones, are accounted for during comparison.
Critical failures are logged and promptly reported to support teams.
APIs and services perform as expected under load.
